

    
    Short instructions for Action Cat:                  
    ----------------------------------
    
 
    System required:
    ---------------
    Amiga 1200 2MB

    Other Amigas:
    If you-ve got 1 MB ChipMem or more, then you-re in with a chance, but
    you will have to start the game from the Workbench.

    If you want to play from disk:
    ------------------------------
    1. Copy each directory (disk1, disk2) to a separate disk.
    2. Give the first disk the name "ActionCat 1".
    3. Give the 2nd disk the name "ActionCat 2".
    4. Copy the file "mathtrans.lib" from the "libs"-folder of your
       harddrive or one of your workbench-diskettes to the "libs"-folder
       on "ActionCat 1".
    5. Reboot with "ActionCat 1" in drive "df0:".

    If you want to play from harddrive:
    -----------------------------------
    Just start the program "Install" in directory "disk1".


    CONTROLS:
    --------
    The game is controlled by Joystick in Port 1

        -LEFT,RIGHT,UP,DOWN : Move as you like.
        -FIRE               : Shoot
        -FIRE AND DOWN      : Activate Mine
        -DOWN               : Activate Teleport

        The Lift section:

        UP and DOWN will move the lift to the wanted stage.

    Keyfunctions:

         -SPACE   : Activate a Nova bomb.
         -Amiga   : Activate a bullet storm.
         -Alt     : Launch a rocket.
         -RETURN  : Activate inventory window.
         -HELP    : Pauses game
         -ESC     : Game over (be warned !)


